key components of the world wide web:
Web browsers: Software apps (chorme,firefox)
Web pages: Documents written in HTML(text,images,videos)
Web servers: Computers that store web content and serve upon request

Distinction between WWW and the internet:
Scope:
the internet is the broader network of connected devices and infrastructure
the WWW is a service that operates on the internet, specifically focused on accessing and sharing info

Tim Berners-Lee -> creator of the internet (computer scientist at CERN)
creations:
HTML(hypertext markup language)
HTTP(hypertext transfer protocol)
URL(Uniform Resource Locator)
the 1st website

Development of Web browsers
The 1st web browsers, including Mosaic and its impact on user experience
the transition from text-based interfaces to graphical web browsers that integrated text.

